Document: RenderSceneData
Path: godot/classes/class_renderscenedata.rst
Summary: Methods for retrieving camera and view data used in rendering scenes.

Method: get_cam_projection() → Projection. Returns the camera projection used to render this frame. Note: If more than one view is rendered, this will return a combined projection.

Method: get_cam_transform() → Transform3D. Returns the camera transform used to render this frame. Note: If more than one view is rendered, this will return a centered transform.

Method: get_uniform_buffer() → RID. Return the RID of the uniform buffer containing the scene data as a UBO.

Method: get_view_count() → int. Returns the number of views being rendered.

Method: get_view_eye_offset(view: int) → Vector3. Returns the eye offset per view used to render this frame. This is the offset between our camera transform and the eye transform.

Method: get_view_projection(view: int) → Projection. Returns the view projection per view used to render this frame. Note: If a single view is rendered, this returns the camera projection. If more than one view is rendered, this will return a projection for the given view including the eye offset.